    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-06-25T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-06-25T14:00:00-05:00" n="80"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d80">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">795.00/6–2550: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Korea</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Muccio</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_niact1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                        </gloss>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Seoul</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-06-26T05:00:00+10:00"
                            >June 26, 1950—5 a. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received June 25—3:46 p. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>944. Sent <gloss target="#t_CINCFE1">CINCFE</gloss>; repeated information
                    Department 944. President has not yet left Seoul (remytel 940, June 26). He has
                    just phoned that he was unable to get through to General MacArthur or to his
                    Chief of Staff<note n="1" xml:id="d80fn1">Maj. Gen. Edward M. Almond.</note> in
                    order to submit an urgent request that 10 F–51s with bombs and bazookas be
                    delivered to Taegu where Korean pilots are awaiting to take off. He hopes that
                    they can be here before dawn. He asserts that unless these planes are here
                    before dawn, it will be very difficult to meet the northern attack.</p>
                <pb facs="0168" n="148" xml:id="pg_148"/>
                <p>In addition, he requests 36 105 mm. howitzers, 36 75 mm. anti-tank guns, and 36
                    155 mm. howitzers.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Muccio</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
